4
00:00:10,639 --> 00:00:12,923
<i>First, make your Product Owner </i>

5
00:00:12,923 --> 00:00:15,000
<i>and your Scrum Master the same person,</i>

6
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:17,623
<i>they basically do the same thing anyway.</i>

7
00:00:18,808 --> 00:00:20,446
<i>Always put the boss on the team,</i>

8
00:00:20,446 --> 00:00:22,395
<i>that keeps developers motivated.</i>

9
00:00:22,395 --> 00:00:26,261
[girl screaming]

10
00:00:26,261 --> 00:00:28,567
<i>Of course, teams should consist of people </i>

11
00:00:28,567 --> 00:00:29,676
<i>with complementary roles </i>

12
00:00:29,676 --> 00:00:31,140
<i>for different parts of the company.</i>

13
00:00:31,140 --> 00:00:32,382
<i>But if budgets get tight,</i>

14
00:00:32,382 --> 00:00:34,805
<i>feel free to leave out QA.</i>

15
00:00:34,805 --> 00:00:35,867
[poof sound]

16
00:00:35,867 --> 00:00:37,653
[collective gasp]

17
00:00:37,653 --> 00:00:39,015
If everyone does their job

18
00:00:39,015 --> 00:00:40,723
then QA is not important.

19
00:00:40,723 --> 00:00:43,069
[small explosion]

20
